{"id":35501,"date":"2021-04-01T17:16:46","date_gmt":"2021-04-01T13:16:46","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=35501"},"modified":"2021-04-01T17:16:46","modified_gmt":"2021-04-01T13:16:46","slug":"gives-everything-away","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/04\/01\/gives-everything-away\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Charity: The Prophet gives everything away before he dies"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Aisha reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, was in the severe agony of his final illness and he had seven or nine gold coins. The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>O Aisha, what have you done with this gold?<\/strong>\u201d I said, \u201cIt is with me.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Give it away in charity.<\/strong>\u201d But I was busy caring for him, and then he said, \u201c<strong>O Aisha, what have you done with this gold?<\/strong>\u201d I said, \u201cIt is with me.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Give it to me.<\/strong>\u201d I brought them and placed them in his hands, then the Prophet said, \u201c<strong>What is Muhammad thinking if he were to meet Allah while holding onto these?<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Ibn H\u0323ibba\u0304n 715<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em>Hasan<\/em> (fair) according to Al-Arna\u2019ut<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064e\u0627 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u062a\u0650 \u0627\u0634\u0652\u062a\u064e\u062f\u0651\u064e \u0648\u064e\u062c\u064e\u0639\u064f \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0648\u0639\u0646\u062f\u0647 \u0